{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_dicorcia_ver01/data/sn82016181/0052904589A/1927012901/0540.xml":{"full_text":"\u2019Change Probes for\nCorner as Loree\nOutwits Bears\nRockefeller Linked With Coup\nin Wheeling Stock; Brokers\nMust Report to Stock Mart\nt flit! d Pri\nNEW YORK That a corner may\nhave been under way in Wheeling\nLake Erie stock, despite continued\ndenials by\ntock Exchange officials.\nWit 3\nintimated again today.\nThe exchange notified members to\nreport the \u201clong\u201d and \u201cshort\u201d posi\ntion of houses and their clients at\nthe close of business on each of the\ntrading days from Jan. 22 to today\nami continue to report until further\nnotice.\nTwo veterans of American finance\nJohn l>. Rockefeller and\nL. F\nLoree\u2014were credited with the sensa\ntional maneuver.\n$2,000,000 Coup\nLunching what appeared to be a\ndetermined battle for control of the\nWheeling Lake Erie road, pre\nsumably for merger with other East\nern lines, these two aged financiers\ncaught hundreds of bears for an es\ntimated loss of the $2,000,000.\nWheeling -ky roeketed\nhigh of $t\nto a new\n0 and closed yesterday\nat $59, five points up for the day\ndav, in which 41,600 shares change!\nhands.\nBehind the scenes stood the sha- l\nflows of Rockefeller and Loree, who\nhave\nbeen buying\nWheeling\nV\nLake Erie for weeks in the face of\nthe insistent short selling by the\nbears mostly\n..young brokers who\nwere in their cradies\nwhen Rocke\nfeller, nearly 90, and Loree, past 70,\nwere recognized as financial leaders.\n510-Mile Line\nThe premium loan value mounted\nto the unusually high price of $1 a\nshar in order to make deliveries\npossible to those who stood to lose\nhuge sums thru having sold short.\nThe stock opened at $57 today, off\ntwo points.\nWall-st had been puzzled for days\nat the gyrations of Wheeling stock,\nboth classes having gone up about\n\"0 points in two weeks.\nThe mer\nger reports explained the jump.\nThe Wheeling operates only about\n540 miles of line, connecting Toledo,\nClevelnd, Zanesville and Wheeling.\nRosy Outlook for Industry\nPainted by Steel Magnate\nSchwab Gives Optimistic Inter\nview\nBefore\nSailing for\nEurope; Steel \u2018Healthy\u2019\nBy United News\nNEW YORK\u2014A rosy outlook for\nAmerican industry and commerce in\n1927\nwas\npainted by Charles M.\nSchwab, chairman of the Bethlehem\nSteel Corporation, just before he\nsailed for Europe\u2019 today on the Ma\njestic.\n\u201cI am optimistic regarding the\nbusiness outlook,\" the magnate said.\nHe\nwas\nparticularly\nbout the steel industry.\nenthusiastic\n\"Tie industry\nas a whole hould\nhave i ve ry flood year,\" Schwab cen\ntinned.\n\u201cSteel prie\nare too low\nand should Ye up.\"\nl'ointiag out that the steel indus\ntry today represents a total invest\nment of\nabout\nwhich the industry\n$.\u25a0>.000,000,000 on\nearning\nL\nmore\nthan\na whole is not\nper\ncent.\nSchwab said steel investors are not\ngetting a\nmones\nproper\nreturn on their\nPrincipal Bans Year B ok\nfor Doubtful Jokes\nBay mine.\nX. J.\nYouth\nav s\nHis\nhiefs Demanded Spicier Humor\nlly Unite d Ni w s\nBAYONNE.\nEcho, yearbook\nN\n.\u2014The\nSenior\nat Bayonne High\nSehool, failed to appear on time yes\nterday when 133 boy and girl grad\nuates were to have received copies\nalong with their diplomas.\nPrincipal Francis A. Brick object\ned to the so-called \"humor page,\"\nedited by Steve Dieckelmann, ami\nordered the Echo held up.\nSteve explained the jokes were not\nhis.\nHe said he submitted a snappy\npanful, but that the editorial board,\nheaded by Leonard Katcher and Ger\ntrude Berk-on, asked spicier jokes.\nFire Tolstoi Home\nMOSCOW\nFireburs attempted to\nset fire to the Count Leo Tolstoi\nhome, pouring kerosene on some of\nTolstoi\u2019s\nmanuscripts.\nwas\nquicekly extinguished\nThe blaze\nCOMFORT AT LAST\u2014Congresswomen need some place to\npowder their noses because it doesn't look very dignified\nin the chamber with the folks gazing down from the gal\nlery.\nHere's Rep. Florence P. Kahn (Cal.) and Edith\nNourse Rogers (Mass.) looking over their own cloakroom.\nAt their left is Robert Richardson, a page.\nInterest in Browning Case Indicates Low\nState of Public Morals, Rabbi Says\n\u2018Peaches\u2019 Is Typical of Money-Mad Flappers of Today Who En\nter Into Matrimony to Get Riches and Pleasure\nThat\ncurrent\ninterest\nin\nthe\nBrowning separation trial is indica\ntive of a low state of public morals,\nand that\ntypical of the\n\"Peaches\u201d\nBrowning is\nmodern money-mad\nflapper was charged by Rabbi J. T.\nLoeb in\na\nsermon today at Ohev\nSholom Temple.\n\u201cThe Browning affair is really the\noutcome of the moral laxity of a\nlarge part of the public, and of a\nvery marked tendency to follow the\npath of least resistance,\u201d the Rabbi\nsaid.\nTremendous Interest\n\u201cPeople are showing a tremendous\ninterest in this case.\nUnder normal\nconditions no such morbid curiosity\nwould be evident.\nThe public has\nmade no protest against the broad\ncasting of the filthy details of this\ntrial, which takes us back to the\ndecadent conditions of old Rome. If\nthings of this nature continue the\nresult must be complete national de\ngeneration.\n\u201cThe trial is a symptom of a dis\neased condition.\nThings that should\nhave been kept from the public are\neagerly devoured by young\nworking untold harm.\ngirl 3,\nThe very at\nmo sphere is saturated with decad\nence.\nHarmed by Prosperity\n\u201cWe see in Browning a man that\nhas been harmed by too much pros\nperity.\nLax morals follow in the\nwake of false emphasis on the pleas\nures of life.\n\u2018Peaches\u2019\nis\ntypical of\nmany\nyoung girls who enter into matr\nmony\nseeking\nriches,\nease\nand\nthings that go with such a union.\u201d\nLack of Faith\nDr. Loeb declared lack of faith in\nfundamentals of religion\nW as\nsponsible for much unhappiness\nthe young people of today.\nre\nin\n\u201cWhen young men of culture and\neducation, with the world\nbefore\nthem. commit suicide, we may well\ninquire as to the cause,\u201d\nhe\n-ad.\n\u201cThe last three weeks have seen sev\neral young men of wealth and hish\nsocial position take their on lives.\nThey were youths without religion,\nwithout a belief in the\ncome.\u201d\nworld to\nSecond Murder May Be\nLaid to Wife-Slayer\nCoffey Willing to 'Tell What I\nKnow if You Tell Me Who's\nMissing;' Wife's Body Found\nNy United Pn sa\nFlATTEVILLE,\nWis,\u2014 Re-ponsi\nbility for a econd murder may be\nplaced on William N. Coffey, who\nyesterday helped oflicers unearth the\ndismembered parts of his wife\u2019s body\nwhich he buried near here.\nSheritT Wright did\nnot disclose\nwhat information he has obtained,\nbut said that in reply to his ques\ntion. concerning a possible prior kill\ning Coffey answered:\n\"Tell me who's missing ami I'll tell\nyou what I know.\"\nRhode Island for Wet Vote\nPROVIDENCE, R. 1. A resolu\ntion requesting Rhode Island's dele\ngation in Congress to support any\nmeasure for a referendum on the\nIXth amendment has been adopted\nby the House of Representatives\nhere.\nC onscience-S trie ken\nTraveler Boosts U. S.\nTreasury Fund $54.25\nT\nHE Treasury\nwas\nincre\nconscience fund\nd $54.25 today.\nSecretary Mellon received the\ncontribution from a Pittsburgh\nman who did not want to cheat\nthe government.\nHe explained he was touring\nEurope with a party several years\nago and when he returned the\nconductor of the group did not\nmake declarations on all his prop\ncity that was taxable.\nNovelty Makers Plan\nto \u2018Cash\u2019 on Browning\nEy Fuited P\u2019reas\nNEW YORK\u2014The Browning\ntrial may be a boon to novelty\nmanufacturers.\nAn Asbury Park (N. J.) firm\nof opportunists advertises in a\nlocal newspaper today as fol\nlows:\n\"Oh, Peache\nThe jokes she\ndidn\u2019t like will make a hit at\nany party now.\nRubber erg\n10c each; bending spoons.\n\u25a0H'\neach; cigars that snow, 9 for\n254\nWorld\u2019s Baby Roundup to\nBe Staged by 101 Ranch\nBr 1 nit d N. w.\nPONCA CITY, Okla.\u2014 Saddle and\nchaps will\ngive\nway to swaddling\nclothes and knes breeches in Mandi\nwhen Miller Bros.' lOl Ranch con\nducts the \"world's first baby round\nup.\"\ni\nYoungsters ranging from those in\narms to 5 years old, will be entered.\nCompetition will\nconsist of events\nlooking to the \"champion kid\" in the\nkiddie car race, \"the world's fastest\ncrawler,\" and kndred championships\nA feature event will be that de\nciding \"the world\u2019s fastest walker\nunder is months.\"\nPacifiers, rattles and remark.' urg\ning them onward will be barred by\njudges. a group of physicians who\nwill conduct a child health contest\nin conjunction with the roundup.\n30 Years in Army\nPORTLAND, Me.\u2014Retired after\nmore\nthan 30 years as an enlisted\nman in the U. S. Army, Sergt. Har\nry Cohen intends to get into the real\nestate business in Florida.\n$100,000 in Gems Stolen\nFrom Indian Potentate\nPart of Loot Recovered from For\nnur\n\\ttendants of Ruler\nB.\nd lri\nCALCUTTA\u2014Jewel., set in ham\nmered gold, long the playthings of\nthe Maharajah of Bharatpur, who\nvalued them at approximately $4100,\n000, have been spirited away from\nhis palace.\nA few of the jewels were recov\nered when an Eurasian and an In\ndian, beiieved former attendants at\nthe Bharatpur court, were arrested\nhere.\n\u2018Old Residents\u2019 of\nAlmshouse Moved\nTransferred to New Combined\nInstitution After as Long as\n41 Years in Alexandria Home\nS arei ll to The\nALEXANDRIA, Va.\nmate., of the city\nThirteen in-1\nalmshouse left\n[early today by train for the new\n1 district home,\nM anassas.\none\nmile north of\nFor many, it was leaving a home\ni they had been accustomed to for\nI\nyears.\n\u201cUncle Josh\" Sherwood, superin\ntendent of the city almshouse for is\nyears, accompanied them. 1\nThe oldest inmate to go is Lizzie:\nPenn.\nShe has been at the home 41\nAunt Lizzie\nyears, and nearly SO.\nhated to break away from \u201cthe old\nhomestead.\u201d\nSeveral have been at the home 15\n1 years.\nI\nPennsylvanians on I.C.C.\nto Be Fought by Neely\nTemple and Pepper, Mentioned'\nfor Post, Would Be Opposed'\nBecause of Lake Rate Case\nOpposition to appointment of uny\nPennsylvanian to the\nCommerce\nCommission\nInterstate\nwas\nex\npressed today by Sen. Neely (Dem.,\nW. Va.), one of the leaders in the\nsuccessful fight against Cyrus\nWoods of that state.\nNeely\u2019s statement followed\nE.\nre\nports that Rep. Temple Rep., Pa.),\n1 had been suggested for the place.\nThere were also reports that\nSen.\nPepper (Bep., Pa.), had been sug\ngested.\nThe West Virginia Senator said\nhis opposition was because of the\npending Lake cargo rate case\nwhich Pennsylvania ami Ohio\nin\nare\nlined up against West Virginia, Vir\nginia, Kentucky and Tennessee.\nBuilding Volume Expected\nto Equal That of 1926\nDrift From Farms to Cities Civen\nas Important Reason\nI Unitis I\u2019r as\nASIIEVILIE, N. C\u2014 The volume\nof construction operations this year\nwill equal the record breaking activi\nties of last, in the opinion of 2000\nof Associ\ndelegates to the meetin\nated General Contractors of America.\nThe prediction is based on the in\ncreasing tendency of population to\ndrift from farms to cities, the obso\nlescence of office and factory build\nings, theaters and schools, making\nary, the elimina\nreplacements nece:\ntion of grade crossings and demands\nfor new roads.\nJail Terms Totaling\n73 Years Meted Out\nI\nJustice Hoehling Puts 18 Be\nhind Bars as Contribution to\nStruggle Against Crime Wave\nJustice Hoehling, District Supreme\nCourt, contributed hi.-, share jester\nday toward breaking up the local\ncrime wave by\nsons to serve a total of\nsentencing IS per\n6 months in prison,\nfollow\nTh\n3 years and\ne sentences\nIra\nSeald\nA.\nGrs\u2014srend. r\n\nlilod Holm.\nKelt Fiids\nCharl Walker\nrobhry. fiv\ny Are\nHobert u. Maxwell\nrobbers, tive seute\nretbeiv, 1X mnenha\nJo J. Harpi\nRoy U. Prebbl.\nhokdup, three san\nWilliam J. Jjekuo\nRihard 1\nholdup threy\nh<\nGardaer\u2014theft\niktige, th\nJa\"s Ashlry\u2014hou-e breaking\nAllert Noipe\nholdup.\nthre\nnt,\ny* ats\nirs.\nfour ATM.\nIF*.\nDanal Matthew- -hokhup, live yeat*\nJams Forley\nWhametom\nloreery. one r.\nWalker\n1.'Kny J. Hopkibe\nW Mb\nthe -uut\ntheit, nin r\nEverett Peris\nAlton Dull\ntheft, IS monthe\nHp it. on\ntheti\nnomihss\nMotion to Draw Pistols\nHalts Escapes in Raid\nThree Alleged Handbook Pa\ntrons Escape, but 23 Per\nsons\nAre\nTaken\nThe motion of detectives in reach\ning for pistols prevented a w holesale\nescape ye-terday during a raid on an\nalleged handbook in a barber shop\nat the rear of 803 North Capitol-st.\nThree\npatrons\nescaped but the\nothers were held until reserves ar\nrived and it was not nec\ndraw a weapon.\nary to\nAlfonso Terruso, 34, the propri\netor, and Joseph Roland, 32, 1020\nFairmont-st nw, were released on\n$2000 bond, charged with handbook\nmaking. Twenty -one men were \"e\nleased as witnesses.\nSteps Urged to Halt High\nMortality Rate Here\nImmediate steps to curb the high\ninfant mortality rate here were urged\non the Commissioners yesterday by a\ndelegation from the Washington\nCouncil\nof Social Agencies. The\nmortality here is X7 deaths per 1000\nlive births.\nThe committee urged .-pending\nmore than $60,000 a year in addi\ntion to present expenditures for child\nhygiene work.\nSaving the children\nis more important than fire or police\nprotection, said Arthur C. Moses,\nchairman.\nSCHOOL BOOKS\nNEW ND I SED 111(41 M 1001. BOOKS\nBIG BOOK SHOP, 933 G St. N. W.\nD.J,\n\nHOME\ncP\na\n17\n2\ni\n1\nK\u2018\n\u201cA\n7\nK\nA\nANTS\nSUITS\n\n8\n\ni\n\u2022'W\n(CHARGE ACCOUNTS iNvnTtO)\n1005 PA.AVE\n\u00bb:-Mi\n1724 PA.AVE. 1\nI\n-r\nStartling Stories of Washington Life\ni\nTHE PAINTED CITY\nBy MARY BADGER WILSON\nW ithin the walls of the Government Buildings goes on\nan intense and fevered life\u2014that of plodding, drab, impe\neunio s government clerks, sleek, pompous Congressmen,\nfaded and impoverished \"old families.\"\nI\nHere they step timidly forth, each with his pale nimbus\nof pathos, or tragedy, humor or romance.\nDrawn with a\ncaustic pen, they uncover a world which is forgotten in the\nbright glare of the \"Painted City.\"\nAt All Bookshops, $2.00\nPublishers\nFREDERICK A. STOKES CO.\nNew Yo-k","height":"21724","width":"14716"}}
